extends ../template

//- Page Variables
block vars
    - var currentpage = "Buttons"

block nav
    include nav
block content


    //- Page Content
    .stcontainer
        span.sttitle Buttons
        p We have the component block into a #[code sass extend] and we extend it on the modifier.
        pre
            code(class="language-css")
                |%btn {
                |    display: inline-block;
                |    line-height: $baselineheight * 2;
                |    color: $buttoncolor;
                |    text-align: center;
                |    vertical-align: middle;
                |    font-size: fs(normal);
                |    white-space: nowrap;
                |    background-color: $buttonbackground;
                |    border-top: $buttonborderwidth $buttonborderstyle $buttonbordercolor;
                |    border-right: $buttonborderwidth $buttonborderstyle $buttonbordercolor;
                |    border-bottom: ($buttonborderwidth * 2) $buttonborderstyle |$buttonbordercolor;
                |    border-left: $buttonborderwidth $buttonborderstyle $buttonbordercolor;
                |    cursor: pointer;
                |    margin:0;
                |    padding-top:   0;
                |    padding-bottom:0;
                |    padding-right:1em;
                |    padding-left: 1em;
                |    border-radius: $radius;
                |    @include transition(all $hovertransition ease-in);

                |    /**
                |    * Nadie quiere un bot√≥n con texto subrayado cuando
                |    * hacemos hover.
                |    */

                |    &:hover {
                |        text-decoration: none;
                |        color: $buttoncolor;
                |    }
                |    &:active,
                |    &:focus{
                |        outline:none;
                |    }
                |    &:visited {
                |    color: $buttoncolor;
                |    }
                |}
        p All buttons comes with the extend #[code %btn] block to look like a button, then, we add the modifier: #[code .btn--modifier]. You should extend the #[code extender] in every partial that uses the buttom.
        p All these #[code %extend] are made to simplify CSS as detailed in #[a(href="https://twitter.com/una") Una Kravets] method #[a(href="http://una.im/classy-css/#üíÅ") Atomic OOBEMITSCSS].
        div
            a.btn--primary(href="#") Modifier: btn--primary
        pre
            code(class="language-html")
                | &lt;a class="btn--primary"&gt;Modifier: btn--primary&lt;/a&gt;

        div
            a.btn--disabled(href="#") Modifier: btn--disabled
        pre
            code(class="language-html")
                | &lt;a class="btn--disabled"&gt;Modifier: btn--disabled&lt;/a&gt;

        div
            a.btn--info(href="#") Modifier: btn--info
        pre
            code(class="language-html")
                | &lt;a class="btn--info"&gt;Modifier: btn--info&lt;/a&gt;

        div
            a.btn--error(href="#") Modifier: btn--error
        pre
            code(class="language-html")
                | &lt;a class="btn--error"&gt;Modifier: btn--error&lt;/a&gt;

        div
            a.btn--warning(href="#") Modifier: btn--warning
        pre
            code(class="language-html")
                | &lt;a class="btn--warning"&gt;Modifier: btn--warning&lt;/a&gt;

        div
            a.btn--success(href="#") Modifier: btn--success
        pre
            code(class="language-html")
